continue_block.description:
Process {process_id} continues execution.

No higher priority or shorter-burst process has arrived.
Block {block_num} of {burst}. Remaining: {remaining}

preemption_burst.description:
Process {new_process} arrives at t={current_time}!

Both have Priority={priority}, but:
- {new_process} original burst: {new_burst}
- {old_process} original burst: {old_burst}

{new_process} has SHORTER original burst → preempts!
{old_process} returns to queue with {old_remaining} blocks remaining.

process_complete.description:
Process {process_id} finishes execution!

Priority: {priority}, Original Burst: {burst}
Started: t={start_time}, Completed: t={end_time}
Waiting time: {wait_time}, Turnaround: {tat}

final.description:
SJF with Priority Scheduling Complete!

Execution Order: {execution_order}

Metrics:
{metrics}

Average Waiting Time: {avg_wait}
Average Turnaround Time: {avg_tat}

Note: ORIGINAL burst was used for all comparisons, not remaining burst.
